Artist Bio:

#Mike Marrero
 Born on the culturally vibrant island of Key West, is a Cuban LatinX. . His super powers are multi-dimensional; visual artist, playwright, and filmmaker. With award winning short films, Buzzcut and Riley Was Here, his talents were showcased at over 100 festivals worldwide. 

This GenXer’s plays have been produced at Guild Hall Center (NY), Repetorio Espanol (NY), Teatro de Centre (Havana), and the Studios of Key West (FL). His original play, Locura, formed the first theatrical exchange aligning the US & Cuba culturally in 60 years. 

Recently his cataloged photographic project, Orisha: The Lost Saints, was awarded a prestigious Knight Foundation Grant and was officially selected to be exhibited at the 2021-2022 Havana Biennial.

Series: GirlsLoveRobots

 #About GOG: 

The Gallery on Greene has consistently fomented curatorial and artistic practice through ambitious exhibitions programs, created in close collaboration with its artists with museums from New York, MCNY, AFAM, SSSM to Havana's National Museum of Fine Art.
